headline: Why Molina Healthcare (MOH) Is Up 15.4% After Completing Its 2025 Buyback Amid Medicaid Profit Concerns
summary: In the past quarter, Molina Healthcare completed its April 2025 share repurchase authorization, buying back 2,849,000 shares for US$499.99 million, while reporting mixed fourth-quarter 2025 results and operational challenges in its Medicaid business. This combination of a fully executed buyback, underwhelming earnings, and analyst concern about Medicaid profitability has sharpened investor focus on the quality and stability of Molina’s earnings profile.
